! This is a lexicon to be used with aspell spell checker only.
! It is at the moment not in use. Remove the string "!aSPell: " if you want to use it.
! Target is to use as many sublexicons as possible with as many variables
! as possible to create aspell affix file.
!aSPell: LEXICON AspellAffix
!aSPell: 
!aSPell: !BISYLLABIC
!aSPell: ! GOAHTI lexicon has consonant gradation and dipthtong simplification
!aSPell: ! Cases: -i, -á, -u, -a, -e, and -o endings
!aSPell: ! Obsolete because GOAHTI has same endings as GADDI ??
!aSPell: !buohkki GOAHTI-IU ;
!aSPell: !buohkká GOAHTI ;
!aSPell: !duohkku GOAHTI-IU ;
!aSPell: !fuohkka GOAHTI ;
!aSPell: !fuohkke GOAHTI ;
!aSPell: !buohkko GOAHTI ;
!aSPell: ! GADDI lexicon has comparative forms
!aSPell: ! Cases: -i, -á, -u, -a, -e, and -o endings
!aSPell: buohkki GADDI ;
!aSPell: cuohkká GADDI ;
!aSPell: duohkku GADDI ;
!aSPell: fuohkka GADDI ;
!aSPell: guohkke GADDI ;
!aSPell: huohkko GADDI ;
!aSPell: ! IIJA non-gradating w/ a-ill
!aSPell: guohkkinymiija IIJA ; ! other case endings?
!aSPell: ! STAHTA non-gradating w/ a/i-ill/
!aSPell: buohkkistáhta STAHTA ;
!aSPell: 
!aSPell: !TRISYLLABIC
!aSPell: ! SEAMU gradating trisyllabic
!aSPell: ! Cases: -i, -a, and -u endings
!aSPell: jealu:jeallum8 SEAMU ;
!aSPell: kuomi:kuopmán8 SEAMU ;
!aSPell: muomu:muopmum8 SEAMU ;
!aSPell: neana:neatnag8 SEAMU ;
!aSPell: ! MALIS gradating w/ consonant endings
!aSPell: ! Cases: -is, -uš, and -ir endings
!aSPell: buohpis:buoh'pis MALIS ;
!aSPell: duohpuš:duoh'puš MALIS ;
!aSPell: goahpir:goah'pir MALIS ;
!aSPell: ! Cases: -is, -uš, and -ir endings
!aSPell: 
!aSPell: !CONTRACTED
!aSPell: ! SUOLU contracted
!aSPell: ! Cases: -u ending only?
!aSPell: suozu:suohccu SUOLU ;
!aSPell: ! FALIS contracted
!aSPell: ! Cases: -is only?
!aSPell: fálggis:fál'gis FALIS ;
!aSPell: 
!aSPell: !MISC
!aSPell: ! LEXDIMINC diminutives
!aSPell: beanáš:beanáž LEXDIMINC ;
!aSPell: 
!aSPell: ! Add more and correct these.

LEXICON NounRoot
  Noun ;
  FirstComponent ;
  HyphNouns ;

LEXICON NonFirstNouns
! some stray affixes, look at these
! Trying them without the initial hyphen
bealis+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only+CmpN/SgLeft+CmpN/SgNomLeft+CmpN/PlGenLeft:beallis LASIS ;
čorgi+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only+CmpN/SgLeft+CmpN/SgNomLeft+CmpN/PlGenLeft:čor'gi GOAHTI-IU ;
giel+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only+CmpN/SgLeft+CmpN/SgNomLeft+CmpN/SgGenLeft+CmpN/PlGenLeft:giel At ;
miese#beaska+CmpN/Last:miese#beas'ka GOAHTI ;
nammasaš+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only+CmpN/SgNomLeft+CmpN/SgGenLeft+CmpN/PlGenLeft:nammas AHKASAS ;
niehkki+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only:niehkki AIGI ;
sahán+CmpN/Last+CmpN/Only:sahám BOAHTIN ;
sis#muotkun:sis#muotkum BOAHTIN ;
!čiegahas:čiegahass JOHTOLAT ; !Especially with numerals, moved to LEXICON SAS

! Yes, this is what they used to look like.
! We remove these obsolete ones if we like the hyphenless ones.
!-bealis:-beallis LASIS ;
!-čorgi:-čor'gi GOAHTI-IU ;
!-giel At ;
!-miese#beaska:-miese#beas'ka GOAHTI ;
!-nammasaš:-nammasažž JOHTOLAT ;
!-niehkki:-niehkki AIGI ;
!-sahán:-sahám BOAHTIN ; !+CmpN/Sg +CmpN/SgLeft +CmpN/SgNomLeft +CmpN/SgGenLeft +CmpN/PlGenLeft
!-sis#muotkun:-sis#muotkum BOAHTIN ; !+CmpN/Sg +CmpN/SgLeft +CmpN/SgNomLeft +CmpN/SgGenLeft +CmpN/PlGenLeft

!čiegahas:čiegahass JOHTOLAT ;

!LEXICON NOUNALSOAFTERNUMBER
!ENDLEX ;
